```

### Animated Gradients
```svg
<linearGradient id="animated-gradient">
  <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#58a6ff">
    <animate attributeName="stop-color" 
             values="#58a6ff;#79c0ff;#58a6ff" 
             dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
  </stop>
</linearGradient>
```

## Color Accessibility

### Contrast Requirements
- Ensure 4.5:1 minimum contrast for normal text
- Achieve 3:1 minimum for large text (18px+)
- Test color combinations with accessibility tools
- Provide fallback colors for critical information

### Color-Blind Considerations
- Don't rely solely on color to convey information
- Use patterns, shapes, or text labels as backup
- Test with color-blind simulation tools
- Avoid problematic red-green combinations

## Color Harmony Rules

### Analogous Schemes
- Use adjacent colors on the color wheel
- Blue → Blue-Purple → Purple progression
- Maintain consistent saturation levels

### Complementary Accents
- Orange (#f0883e) complements Blue (#58a6ff)
- Use sparingly for high-impact elements
- Apply to call-out boxes or important status indicators

### Monochromatic Depth
- Vary lightness/darkness of single hue
- Create depth through opacity and saturation
- Use for section backgrounds and containers